      • bitSetInfo

        public void bitSetInfo()
        Spits out information about java.util.BitSet BitSet is so weird, not reporting its set size, but rather size based on the machine implementation or length based on which bits are set. Here is an example of BitSet size of 4. "BitSet weirdness: bitSet={1}, bitSet.length=2, bitSet.size=64, bitSetSize=4"

        This test is a legacy artifact from when the first implementation was based on BitSet.
